The Police in Kano has arrested Suleiman Musa, 19, in Ungogo Local Government Area for stabbing Abubakar Sani, 18. The Public Relations Officer, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, confirmed the arrest in a statement on Wednesday. Haruna said the incident occurred on April 7, at Sharifai Quarters of Ugogo Local Government Area. A complaint from Sharifa Quarters said that on the same date, the suspect stabbed Sani of the same address on his stomach with a knife. The victim was rushed to Murtala Muhammad Specialist Hospital, Kano. He was confirmed dead by a medical doctor on April 10. The spokesman added that the suspect had a misunderstanding with the deceased. The Commissioner of Police, Samaâ€™ila Dikko, has ordered that the case be transferred to the Criminal Investigation Department (CID), Homicide Section.